reviews.review: Absolutely amazing! Abrams did not hold back with this film. From the cinematography, to the booming sound effects, this Star Wars film should not be missed. I can't wait to see it again!

It was...a lot. There were many inexplicable storyline decisions and random threads that went nowhere. As a lifelong fan, disappointed that there werenâ€™t clear narratives tying the last three films together.

As someone who disliked episode 7 and was indifferent  toward 8, I wasn't expecting very much from the movie. I was pleasantly surprised, the movie had a good pace, some gorgeous scenes, and felt more like a Star Wars movie to me than the last film and didn't borrow the plot like 7. Full of moments that keep you on the edge of your seat and fun hidden treats for fans. My favorite of the new trilogy by a long shot.

The end of a saga. Maybe the most important film saga in cinema history. Lots of fan service. Almost entirely ignores TLJ, which I'm sure will be disappointing to some. Really wish JJ Abrams had directed all 3 films, but such is life. It definitely had the feel and spirit of a Star Wars film. I will absolutely be seeing it again.
A great action packed ending to the Skywalker Saga.
I liked it. Good conclusion to the skywalker saga. Tho I did like the last jedi better

I am a Long term Star Wars fan, one who does admittedly like the sequels (excluding the garbage that is canto bight), and in in my relatively humble opinion, this movie, this is beautiful, the writing is solid, featuring subtle foreshadowing, character development, and twists that aren't obvious but also make sense. Pair this with some fantastic acting, directing, and cinematography, as well as the exemplary ability to bring a smooth end to the whole saga, including the whole saga and without painful references, one finds a film that is outright fantastic for a fan, and an exceedingly good movie for a newcomer. So if you were to follow what I say, I'd recommend you watch the movie, and follow the love of the fans and viewers, not the ratings of critics that are based not in opinion, but in the usual regard to something new in Star Wars, regardless of this being a clear exception to Disney's usual lack of artistic creativity, and think about giving a rating like mine, to show that a fan appreciates a legitimate good film and that we want more. But that's just my opinion, it's art, ergo subjective. So please keep this in mind when talking about the movie, differentiate opinion and fact, whether you agree or disagree with me, because I want to love the  community of Star Wars that I'm a part of. If you got this far, thanks for reading, I appreciate it.

-Sincerely, a random person

Forget the critics. This is a great Star Wars film. Sure, a few things didn't quite land or make complete sense, but it had all the feels and did everything I want a Star Wars movie to do. Can't wait to go again.

I am so happy they tied everything together. The Last Jedi was not great in my opinion. This episode helped fix many of the holes from that movie and did so in the fun way that I have came to expect from Star Wars. My 8 and 10 year old boys loved it too.
